properties.areaDesc: North Snowy Range Foothills; South Laramie Range
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 24 at 8:36PM MST until January 26 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West to southwest winds 35 to 45 MPH with occasional
gusts 55 to 60 MPH possible.

* WHERE...Interstate 80 near Arlington and Elk Mountain, as well
as the Summit between Laramie and Cheyenne.

* WHEN...From Saturday afternoon through Sunday morning.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Hazardous travel with an
enhanced blow over risk for light and high profile vehicles,
including camping and tractor trailers.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH SUNDAY MORNING
